### something extra 
Running with systemd (Optional, for Persistence)
You can use systemd to keep the chat app running in the background and start it on boot.
Create a unit file (as root):
sudo nano /etc/systemd/system/lan-chat.service


Example unit file:
[Unit]
Description=LAN Chat Flask App
After=network.target

[Service]
User=YOUR_USERNAME
WorkingDirectory=/home/YOUR_USERNAME/chat_app
Environment="PATH=/home/YOUR_USERNAME/chat_app/venv/bin"
ExecStart=/home/YOUR_USERNAME/chat_app/venv/bin/python app.py
Restart=always

[Install]
WantedBy=multi-user.target


Replace YOUR_USERNAME and paths accordingly.
Reload systemd, enable and start:
sudo systemctl daemon-reload
sudo systemctl enable lan-chat.service
sudo systemctl start lan-chat.service


Check status:
sudo systemctl status lan-chat.service
Now your chat app will run automatically on boot and stay up in the background.
